HEADWORD: Chieftain
<hw>Chief"tain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cheftayn</ets>, <ets>chevetayn</ets>, OF. <ets>chevetain</ets>, F.
<ets>capitaine</ets>, LL. <ets>capitanus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>caput</ets>
head. Cf. <er>Captain</er>, and see <er>chief</er>.]</ety> <def>A
captain, leader, or commander; a chief; the head of a troop, army, or
clan.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Chief; commander; leader; head. See
<er>Chief</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

